  2862→  // TODO(emilio): We could avoid some refcount traffic here, specially in the
  2863→  // ComputedStyle case, which uses atomic refcounting.
  2864→  //
  2865→  // Hold the ComputedStyle alive, because it could become a dangling pointer
  2866→  // during the replacement. In practice it's not a huge deal, but better not
  2867→  // playing with dangling pointers if not needed.
