  "text": "## CSS Style Change to Layout Paint Chain in Mozilla Firefox\n\n### Overview\nThis document traces the complete chain from CSS style change notification through layout reflow to display list construction and WebRender layer updates in Mozilla Firefox/Gecko.\n\n### Stage 1: Style Change Notification\n\n**Files:** `layout/style/ServoStyleSet.cpp`, `layout/style/ServoStyleSet.h`\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `ServoStyleSet::RuleAdded()` - Notifies the style system when a CSS rule is added\n- `ServoStyleSet::RuleChanged()` - Notifies when an existing rule is modified\n- `ServoStyleSet::RuleRemoved()` - Notifies when a rule is removed\n\nThese functions trigger style invalidation by calling `RuleChangedInternal()` which marks the style sheet as dirty and posts invalidations to the Servo stylist.\n\n### Stage 2: Style Recomputation and Frame Style Recomputation\n\n**Files:** `layout/style/RestyleManager.cpp`, `layout/style/RestyleManager.h`, `layout/style/ServoStyleSet.cpp`\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `ServoStyleSet::StyleDocument()` (ServoStyleSet.cpp:809) - Initiates the style traversal of the document tree by calling Servo's `Servo_TraverseSubtree()`\n- `RestyleManager::ProcessPendingRestyles()` (RestyleManager.cpp:3284) - Public entry point for processing style changes\n- `RestyleManager::DoProcessPendingRestyles()` (RestyleManager.cpp:3087) - Core implementation that orchestrates the style traversal and post-traversal\n- `RestyleManager::ProcessPostTraversal()` (RestyleManager.cpp:2747) - Processes the results of style traversal and extracts change hints\n\n**Data Structures:**\n- `nsStyleChangeList` (nsStyleChangeList.h) - Holds a list of `nsStyleChangeData` elements containing frames, content, and change hints\n- `nsStyleChangeData` - Contains the frame, content, and `nsChangeHint` indicating what needs to be updated\n\n**Change Hint Extraction:**\nIn `ProcessPostTraversal()`, the function calls `Servo_TakeChangeHint()` to retrieve change hints from Servo indicating what layout/paint operations are needed, then appends these to the `nsStyleChangeList`.\n\n### Stage 3: Dirty Frame Reflow Scheduling\n\n**Files:** `layout/style/RestyleManager.cpp`, `layout/base/PresShell.cpp`\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `RestyleManager::ProcessRestyledFrames()` (RestyleManager.cpp:1548) - Processes each entry in the change list\n- `StyleChangeReflow()` (RestyleManager.cpp:1326) - Static function that schedules a reflow for frames that need it. Determines the appropriate dirty bits (`NS_FRAME_IS_DIRTY` or `NS_FRAME_HAS_DIRTY_CHILDREN`) and intrinsic size dirty flags based on the change hint\n- `PresShell::FrameNeedsReflow()` (PresShell.cpp:2632) - Core reflow scheduling function that:\n  - Adds dirty bits to the frame\n  - Marks intrinsic sizes as dirty on ancestors and descendants as needed\n  - Adds the frame to `mDirtyRoots` list\n  - Calls `SetNeedLayoutFlush()` to schedule a layout flush\n\n### Stage 4: Reflow Execution\n\n**Files:** `layout/base/PresShell.cpp`, `layout/generic/ReflowInput.cpp`\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `PresShell::ProcessReflowCommands()` (PresShell.cpp:10637) - Processes the queued dirty roots:\n  - Calls `WillDoReflow()` before reflow\n  - Iterates through `mDirtyRoots` and calls `DoReflow()` for each\n  - Calls `DidDoReflow()` after all reflows complete\n  - Returns whether reflow was interrupted\n- `PresShell::DoReflow()` (PresShell.cpp:10438) - Performs the actual reflow of a frame and its descendants\n- `PresShell::DidDoReflow()` (PresShell.cpp:10365) - Post-reflow operations including reflow callbacks and suppression management\n\n**ReflowInput:** `layout/generic/ReflowInput.cpp` and `.h` contain the reflow input data structure that carries constraint information through the reflow process.\n\n### Stage 5: Display List Construction\n\n**Files:** `layout/painting/nsDisplayList.cpp`, `layout/painting/nsDisplayList.h`, `layout/base/PresShell.cpp`\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `PresShell::PaintInternal()` (PresShell.cpp:6467) - Paint entry point that calls into the frame painting system\n- `nsLayoutUtils::PaintFrame()` - Triggers display list construction for a frame and its descendants\n- `nsDisplayList::PaintRoot()` (nsDisplayList.cpp/h) - Entry point for display list construction\n- `BuildDisplayListForStackingContext()` - Virtual method on frame classes that builds the display list for a stacking context\n\nThe display list construction process:\n1. Creates a `nsDisplayListBuilder` to manage the construction\n2. Calls `BuildDisplayListForStackingContext()` on frames recursively\n3. Each frame appends `nsDisplayItem` objects to the display list\n4. The display list represents all drawable elements in painting order\n\n### Stage 6: WebRender Layer Update\n\n**Files:** `gfx/layers/wr/WebRenderLayerManager.cpp`, `gfx/layers/wr/WebRenderCommandBuilder.cpp`\n\n**Key Functions:**\n- `WebRenderLayerManager::EndTransactionWithoutLayer()` (WebRenderLayerManager.cpp:338) - Orchestrates the conversion of the display list to WebRender commands:\n  - Creates a `wr::DisplayListBuilder`\n  - Calls `mWebRenderCommandBuilder.BuildWebRenderCommands()` to convert display items\n  - Handles resource updates and scroll data\n  - Calls `WrBridge()->EndTransaction()` to send the commands to the WebRender compositor\n\n- `WebRenderCommandBuilder::BuildWebRenderCommands()` (WebRenderCommandBuilder.cpp:1844) - Converts a display list item to WebRender commands\n- `WebRenderCommandBuilder::CreateWebRenderCommandsFromDisplayList()` (WebRenderCommandBuilder.cpp:1994) - Recursively processes display list items and generates WebRender drawing commands\n\n**WebRender Integration:**\n- Uses `wr::DisplayListBuilder` (C++ binding to Rust WebRender)\n- Handles `CreateWebRenderCommands()` virtual method on display items\n- Manages scroll data, transforms, clips, and other rendering state\n- Sends the final display list to the GPU process for rendering\n\n### Complete Call Chain Summary\n\nThe complete call chain is:\n```\nServoStyleSet::RuleAdded/Changed\n  ↓\nServoStyleSet::StyleDocument (calls Servo_TraverseSubtree)\n  ↓\nRestyleManager::ProcessPendingRestyles\n  ↓\nRestyleManager::DoProcessPendingRestyles\n  ↓\nRestyleManager::ProcessPostTraversal (extracts change hints)\n  ↓\nRestyleManager::ProcessRestyledFrames\n  ↓\nStyleChangeReflow\n  ↓\nPresShell::FrameNeedsReflow (marks dirty, schedules reflow)\n  ↓\nPresShell::ProcessReflowCommands\n  ↓\nPresShell::DoReflow (performs reflow)\n  ↓\nPresShell::DidDoReflow\n  ↓\nPresShell::PaintInternal\n  ↓\nnsDisplayList::PaintRoot\n  ↓\nnsIFrame::BuildDisplayListForStackingContext (builds display list)\n  ↓\nWebRenderLayerManager::EndTransactionWithoutLayer\n  ↓\nWebRenderCommandBuilder::BuildWebRenderCommands\n  ↓\nWebRenderCommandBuilder::CreateWebRenderCommandsFromDisplayList\n  ↓\nWrBridge()->EndTransaction (sends to GPU process)\n```\n\nThis chain implements the critical path from style invalidation through rendering, enabling efficient incremental updates of the display in response to CSS changes."
